                <note rend="inline" type="source">Secretary’s Daily Meetings, Lot 58 D 609, June
                        1951<note n="1" xml:id="d388fn1">Chronological collection of the records of
                        the Secretary of State’s daily meetings with top Department of State
                        officials for the years 1949–1952, as maintained by the Special Assistant to
                        the Secretary of State.</note>
                </note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Director of the Executive
                        Secretariat</hi> (<hi rend="italic">McWilliams</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]<note n="2" type="source" xml:id="d388fn2">The
                            omitted sections summarized discussions of the Korean situation and
                            Iran.</note>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-06-12">June 12,
                            1951</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">Subject: Summary of Meeting With the Secretary</p>
                <p>
                    <table>
                        <row>
                            <cell rendition="#top #nowrap">Participants:</cell>
                            <cell>Mr. Acheson</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell/>
                            <cell>Mr. Matthews<note n="3" xml:id="d388fn3">H. Freeman Matthews,
                                    Deputy Under Secretary of State.</note>
                            </cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell/>
                            <cell>Mr. Cabot<note n="4" xml:id="d388fn4">Thomas D. Cabot, Director of
                                    International Security Affairs in the Department of
                                    State.</note>
                            </cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell/>
                            <cell>Mr. Nitze<note n="5" xml:id="d388fn5">Paul H. Nitze, Director of
                                    the Policy Planning Staff in the Department of State.</note>
                            </cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell/>
                            <cell>Mr. Barrett<note n="6" xml:id="d388fn6">Edward W. Barrett,
                                    Assistant Secretary of State for Public Affairs.</note>
                            </cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell/>
                            <cell>Mr. Thorp</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell/>
                            <cell>Mr. Howe<note n="7" xml:id="d388fn7">Fisher Howe, Deputy Special
                                    Assistant for Intelligence.</note>
                            </cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell/>
                            <cell>Mr. Reinhardt<note n="8" xml:id="d388fn8">G. Frederick Reinhardt,
                                    Director of the Office of Eastern European Affairs in the
                                    Department of State.</note>
                            </cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell/>
                            <cell>Mr. McWilliams</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell/>
                            <cell>Mr. Battle<note n="9" xml:id="d388fn9">Lucius D. Battle, Special
                                    Assistant to the Secretary of State.</note>
                            </cell>
                        </row>
                    </table>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>Item 3. <hi rend="italic">Status of Work on Kem Amendment</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Secretary asked Mr. Thorp about the status of the work on the Kem Amendment.
                    Mr. Thorp reported (1) that the Secretary of Defense had compiled his list which
                    covered some seventeen hundred general category items with many sub-heads under
                    each; (2) the general statement of exception had been drawn for submission to
                    the Congress and he thought that the language was very good; and, (3) the
                    Regional Bureaus began a series of discussions with the various ambassadors
                    yesterday to explain the law to them and the request for information on which
                    the <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> could base action for each country.</p>
                <p>It was generally agreed by everyone present that this was a pretty awful mess and
                    almost impossible for us to administer.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. J. <hi rend="smallcaps">McWilliams</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
